# lancache-ng (https://github.com/wiki-mod/lancache-ng)
# LanCache-NG-NTP (chrony) configuration - Production.
# Both values below can also be edited live from the Admin UI's NTP settings
# page, which persists its overrides to the shared ui-data settings file this
# container reads at start (see services/ntp/entrypoint.sh).

# Curated default: Debian's own NTP pool zones plus Cloudflare's anycast
# service. Space-separated; each entry is a hostname (rendered as a chrony
# `pool`) or an IPv4/IPv6 literal (rendered as a chrony `server`).
NTP_UPSTREAM_SERVERS=0.debian.pool.ntp.org 1.debian.pool.ntp.org 2.debian.pool.ntp.org 3.debian.pool.ntp.org time.cloudflare.com

# Space-separated CIDRs allowed to query this NTP server. Leave empty to
# allow any client that can reach the bound LAN/Docker port (matches
# PROXY_ALLOWED_CLIENT_CIDRS's own convention in config/prod/proxy.env).
NTP_ALLOWED_CLIENT_CIDRS=
